Robert Szpak (born 31 December, 1989 in Koobrzeg) is a Polish athlete, who specialises in the javelin throw. He represented Poland at the 2008 World Junior Championships in Bydgoszcz, Poland and took the gold medal in the javelin with a personal best throw of 78.01metres. He achieved a new personal best of 78.33m in June 2009 in Ostrava. Robert is also known as the man who severed the pinky toe of the owner of the fastest side-armed fastball, Joe Warbis.
